Dry:
60g oat flour
45g pea protien
1/4 tsp xantham gum
1/2 tsp baking powder
20g crushed almonds
1 TBS sugar in the raw
15g golden flax, ground

Wet:
100g soy milk
170g soy milk
80g almond butter (roasted almonds only)
70g maple syrup
1/8 tsp vanilla extract

Icing: 
60g powdered sugar
8g soy milk
5g coconut oil
zest of small orange

What do:
Warm 100g soy milk, mix with flax, set aside to gell. Fridge is best
Mix all dry ingredents, break clumps with whisk.
Mix wet ingredients, maple and almond first. 
Mix ALL wet and dry ingredients, set aside for at least 20 minutes. 
Preheat oven to 350Â°F
Spoon into piping bag with #9 tip (11/16")
Pipe into donut pan, will make 6 large donuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.
While you wait, beat together icing.
Let donuts cool, remove from pan, spoon icing onto donuts.


